    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:1.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—",
          "en": "So I have heard. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:1.2",
          "pli": "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
          "en": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:1.3",
          "pli": "Atha kho aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. ",
          "en": "Then, late at night, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:1.4",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
          "en": "and recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:2.1",
          "pli": "“Ādittasmiṃ agārasmiṃ, ",
          "en": "“When your house is on fire, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:2.2",
          "pli": "yaṃ nīharati bhājanaṃ; ",
          "en": "you rescue the pot "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:2.3",
          "pli": "Taṃ tassa hoti atthāya, ",
          "en": "that’s useful, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:2.4",
          "pli": "no ca yaṃ tattha ḍayhati. ",
          "en": "not the one that’s burnt. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:3.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ ādittako loko, ",
          "en": "And as the world is on fire "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:3.2",
          "pli": "jarāya maraṇena ca; ",
          "en": "with old age and death, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:3.3",
          "pli": "Nīharetheva dānena, ",
          "en": "you should rescue by giving, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:3.4",
          "pli": "dinnaṃ hoti sunīhataṃ. ",
          "en": "for what’s given is rescued. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:4.1",
          "pli": "Dinnaṃ sukhaphalaṃ hoti, ",
          "en": "What’s given has happiness as its fruit, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:4.2",
          "pli": "nādinnaṃ hoti taṃ tathā; ",
          "en": "but not what isn’t given. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:4.3",
          "pli": "Corā haranti rājāno, ",
          "en": "Bandits take it, or rulers, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:4.4",
          "pli": "aggi ḍahati nassati. ",
          "en": "it’s consumed by fire, or lost. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:5.1",
          "pli": "Atha antena jahati, ",
          "en": "Then in the end this corpse is cast off, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:5.2",
          "pli": "Sarīraṃ sapariggahaṃ; ",
          "en": "along with all your possessions. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:5.3",
          "pli": "Etadaññāya medhāvī, ",
          "en": "Knowing this, a clever person "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:5.4",
          "pli": "Bhuñjetha ca dadetha ca; ",
          "en": "would enjoy what they have and also give it away. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:5.5",
          "pli": "Datvā ca bhutvā ca yathānubhāvaṃ, ",
          "en": "After giving and using according to their means, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.41:5.6",
          "pli": "Anindito saggamupeti ṭhānan”ti. ",
          "en": "blameless, they go to a heavenly place.”"
        }
      ],
